MESSAGE.value: Changes: -- Content Manager now returns the content is has loaded when using the load methods this is opposed to using load then get -- Physics stuff has gone, I will work on this properly -- Some documentation clean up -- Example game, input handler and state have been made -- The example state shows loading content, the particle system and input handling -- Removed controller stuff, this will be revised at a later date -- Removed reference to the Input handler in states (can be retrieved via game.getEngine().getInputHandler() -- Changed the Animation constructor to take a texture rather than a String key -- Various cleanups
Removed the Shapes class as for some reason it wasn't deleted before I am rewriting this

Changes: Engine -- Made the Particle class package-private as no one really needs to use it -- Moved Particle.Configuration to ParticleConfig to allow Particle to be package-private -- Changed the Configuration to LauncherConfig for clarity -- Placeholder Physics classes (RigidBody, World, Pair, Polygon, BodyConfig etc.) Game -- Added some controller testing code to ExampleInput
Bugs: -- Cannot find monitor refresh rate properly for some reason -- Wouldn't really call this a bug, but the title gets overwritten by the FPS counter
90% finished Menu, Just need to change origin of spinning squares and talk about font with everyone as well as colours.
